at make the friend a distinct social actor; failed friendship; and friendships in narratives such as those of Ruth and Naomi, and Jonathan and David. Olyan presents a comprehensive look at what constitutes friendship in the Hebrew Bible.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aFriendshipxBiblical teaching. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / Old Testament.2bisacsh1 aCollins, John, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2017z9783110548259oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106389810 cprintz978030018268240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300184228423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300184228/original  a978-3-11-063898-1  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017